.TH "xemaclite_aligned_write" 9 "xemaclite_aligned_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xemaclite_aligned_write \- Write from 16-bit aligned to 32-bit aligned address
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xemaclite_aligned_write
.BI "(void *src_ptr "  ","
.BI "u32 *dest_ptr "  ","
.BI "unsigned length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src_ptr" 12
Void pointer to the 16-bit aligned source address
.IP "dest_ptr" 12
Pointer to the 32-bit aligned destination address
.IP "length" 12
Number bytes to write from source to destination
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function writes data from a 16-bit aligned buffer to a 32-bit aligned
address in the EmacLite device.
